nts, concentrates very well, solves problems extremely well, takes responsibility seriously.\n- **Weaknesses:** Regarded as arrogant/know\u2011it\u2011all, has a hot temper, relatively weak leadership skills.\n- **Implications:** Strong problem\u2011solving and concentration suggest competence under pressure, but the arrogance, hot temper, and weak leadership raise red flags for teamwork and crew morale.\n**Overall assessment:**\n- **Calmness under pressure** is clearly demonstrated for B (handles stress well) and C (keeps calm in a crisis). A and D only have indirect indications.\n- **Decision\u2011making and technical competence** are solid for A (anticipation, spatial vision), B (weather assessment, computer skills), C (quick correct decisions, tech understanding), and D (problem solving).\n- **Teamwork/communication** is strongest for A (very good leadership) but undermined by unfriendly behavior; B\u2019s teamwork is questionable due to nasty remarks; C\u2019s communication difficulties and egocentric attitude are significant; D\u2019s arrogance and hot temper are detrimental.\n- **Professional development**: B shows conscientiousness and no stated resistance to learning; C is not willing to further his education; A is not open to new ideas; D\u2019s arrogance may limit growth.\nBalancing these factors, **Candidate\u202fB** offers the best combination of reliability, stress resilience, technical ability, and a baseline of professionalism, with weaknesses that are more manageable (memory for numbers can be supported by checklists; interpersonal issues can be mitigated through crew\u2011resource\u2011training). The other candidates each have a more serious deficit in either calmness, teamwork, or long\u2011term development.\n**My vote:** Candidate\u202fB.\nMETADATA_JSON:\n{\"agent\": \"agent_2\", \"vote\": \"Candidate B\"}", "thoughts": "We have gathered info from agents 1 and 3 about D and A. Now we need to contribute our own analysis, possibly ask about other c